Source: Penguin History of New Zealand
Author: Michael King
Vol / Page: 405
Edition:
Quote: Tangata whenua people already swallowed up by urban expansion...were unwilling to let people from other tribal backgrounds make use of existing marae. This, coupled with the absence of marae in new suburbs, led to the conception and development of urban marae.
